text:
<@U02E3CRMA> and <@U0EL0GLEL> obviously the wall is on!  Thank you.  Two clarifications:
1.  Are you planning to leave on over night or be in by 9 tomorrow to turn back on?  i ask cuz we are doing camera tests (Ewald coming all the way in, just for this) at 9am.
2.  Any caveats about the wall we should know?  I’d love to demo touch and lighting.  It’s been a while for me.  I kinda miss this thing
I will be here that time tomorrow, probably 8:00 or so need to update the mosaic software for the right cubby on that display
I take it even is mosaic not updated we will be able to observe on screen flicker
No we are doing camera test to what mode see we have to shoot on to not detect any screen flickering. Normal video stuff :)
They just need to be on.
Ah, that's what I thought. Yeah normal video stuff, cool.
Just wanna be able to test so we show up on site ready to roll.
even without the Mosaic we can do a full test tomorrow morning - with respect to content and screen frame rate we're at parity with the SBO install.
with Peter's updates to Mosaic we can test cubby interaction choreography and get a jump on any blocking you might want to have figured out going into the shoot

<@U0ML49XU0> one thing I'd like to check tomorrow is if we're seeing any flicker from the LED strips on video. The Arduino PWM logic _might_ cause some flicker, but there's a couple tricks I can play to work around it if needed.
Great call joel. That's exactly what we are looking for. Thanks.
